Skip VERSION/SOVERSION under emscripten so every NEEDED entry
is the bare "libhdf5.so" fixing deduplication by string
identity. This fixes the associated dimscale test in h5py.

Here is the likely mechanism:

When CMake stamps VERSION/SOVERSION on libhdf5, libhdf5_hl
records NEEDED = libhdf5.so.310.5.1 while consumers that link
with bare -lhdf5 record NEEDED = libhdf5.so. Contrary to
native platforms, the loader on emscripten-forge currently
seems to treat the two strings as distinct libraries, loads
libhdf5 twice. That breaks the HDF5 metadata cache. This
mechanism was inferred by putting debug statements throughout
the hdf5 codebase and observing the behavior of the metadata
cache until two addresses showed up where we should only have
one per hdf5 instance.

A general fix would be better, this one should be considered a
temporary workaround and can be dropped as soon as a better
solution is available.


--- a/config/cmake/HDF5Macros.cmake
+++ b/config/cmake/HDF5Macros.cmake
@@ -22,10 +22,10 @@
     else ()
       set (LIBHDF_VERSION ${HDF5_${libpackage}_PACKAGE_SOVERSION_MAJOR})
     endif ()
-    set_target_properties (${libtarget} PROPERTIES VERSION ${PACKAGE_SOVERSION})
+    if (NOT EMSCRIPTEN)
+      set_target_properties (${libtarget} PROPERTIES VERSION ${PACKAGE_SOVERSION})
+    endif ()
     if (WIN32)
         set (${LIB_OUT_NAME} "${LIB_OUT_NAME}-${LIBHDF_VERSION}")
-    else ()
+    elseif (NOT EMSCRIPTEN)
         set_target_properties (${libtarget} PROPERTIES SOVERSION ${LIBHDF_VERSION})
     endif ()
